<p id="para">
	Note that <b>Turn Watcher</b> works in 640x480 in 16 colors
	(though in 16 colors, the icons will <i>look</i> broken.)
	If you have an old computer you'd like to use and the
	best resolution is only 640x480, <b>Turn Watcher</b>
	will work for you! And don't forget that <b>Turn Watcher</b>
	works under Linux...
</p>

<p id="para">
	We recommand a minimum resolution of 800x600
	and a minimum of 65 thousand colors (16 bits).
</p>

<p id="para">
	We suggest 1024x768 and a video card which supports
	<i>True&nbsp;Color</i> for best performances.
</p>

